description:
Responsibilities: 

Manage and lead the planning and implementation of IT technical projects (e.g. Cloud implementation, IT infrastructure projects);
Manage project schedule, resources and risks. Perform proper escalation to ensure project success;
Ensure all the contractual commitments and deliverable are successfully delivered by vendors on time and within the budget;
Conduct system analysis, implementation, testing, user training and documentation on IT systems;
Interface with customers on system implementation for business systems projects;
Perform product evaluation, vendor selection, and procurement of IT solutions / products. 

Requirement:

Degree in IT/ Computer Sciences/ Computer Engineering or related discipline
5 years solid experience in IT project management with technical knowledge;
Certified in any PMP, Agile, or Scrum Master is preferred
Key competencies:
Leading others 
Composure
Interpersonal Savvy 
Business Acumen
Dealing with Ambiguity

We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity.  Free company coach is provided. Interested parties, please quote our reference number and apply with full resume, present and expected salary, by clicking "APPLY NOW". 


We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for consideration of your application for the relevant post within the HGC Global Communications Limited. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly according to our Personal Information Collection Statement, a copy of which will be available upon written request. Information of unsuccessful candidates will be destroyed within six months.

Responsibilities:

Participate in the development of the company’s server, complete the design, development and programming tasks of the corresponding software with high quality;
Develop and improve the speed and scalability of existing trading systems;
Daily maintenance of the existing system to ensure the safety and stability of the application system;
Assist in providing training to juniors;
Report to China team-lead.

 Requirements:

Bachelor degree in Information Technology or related discipline.
2 years’ experience of C++ programming language development and related development and debugging tools;
Proficient in network protocol TCP, UDP, HTTP/WebSocket protocol, network programming and multi-threaded programming, with high concurrent service development experience;
Master MySQL, PostgreSQL, Redis and LevelDB, be able to design database tables independently and optimize SQL statements;
Proficient in Windows/Linux system, especially in C++11, with enthusiasm for solving practical business problems with new technical methods;
Have strong sense of responsibility, good at logical and systematical thinking;
Experience in large-scale financial transaction system development is highly preferred;
Great interest in exploring Fintech industry;
Energetic with can-do attitude and team spirit;
Strong communication and presentation skills in Chinese and Mandarin.
IANG is welcomed.
We provide competitive package to the right candidates:

5 days work
Discretionary bonus
13-21 days annual leave
Marriage leave
Compassionate leave
Medical insurance
Dental scheme
WFH policy
Unlimited snacks and drinks provided
Periodic tea time gathering
Staff team building activities
and more...

Job Descriptions:

Define, document and translate business requirements into system specification;
Perform analysis, design, programming and testing following system development life cycle (SDLC) methodology and adhering to corporate-wise technology standards;
Adhere to the development processes including coding standards, technical; documentation standards, QA processes, configuration management;
Work closely in team-environment and meet project schedules; and
Keep good communication and coordination with team members.

Requirements:

Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or related disciplines;
Knowledge in Microsoft .NET Framework (C#) or JavaScript in Web programming;
Fluent in applying SQL statements for data manipulations;
Good command of written and spoken in Chinese and English;
Fresh graduate is welcomed to apply; and
Immediately available is highly preferable.

We offer five-day work week, attractive career opportunities, remuneration and benefits to the right candidates. Interested applicants, please submit detailed resume with current & expected salary and date of availability to Human Resources Department by clicking the below Apply Now. 

(For more information about our Company, please visit our website www.esrichina.hk)
