AUGMENTED CREATIVITY LAB

Senior AI Research Engineer / AI Research Engineer (in the rank of Research Fellow / Senior Research Assistant / Research Assistant) (PR0443/21-22)

The Augmented Creativity Lab at Hong Kong Baptist University invites applications for the Senior AI Research Engineer / AI Research Engineer position. The selected candidates will work with a group of renowned interdisciplinary researchers, focusing on an AI-based Art Tech project addressing human-machine co-creativity research. More information about the project could be found at https://research.hkbu.edu.hk/highlighted-projects/building-platform-technologies-for-symbiotic-creativity-in-hong-kong.

The appointees are expected to perform the following roles:
Develop new algorithms for AI art content generation using Deep Learning;
Develop demo/system/platform of symbiotic performance incorporating with AI system engineer, AI scientist and artist; and
Write paper/patent and release open source code.
Potential candidates should have/be:

PhD or master’s degree in Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Information Engineering, Mathematics or relevant disciplines with substantial years of related experience. Candidates with less experience but with strong research record may also be considered;
Solid R&D experience in one or more of the following domains: content generation, NLP, computer vision, etc.;
Familiar with deep learning/algorithms, especially on foundation model, transformer model, GANs, GNNs, RL, etc.;
Familiar with deep learning frameworks of PyTorch/TensorFlow, GPU programming of CUDA. Knowledge of Mindspore is a plus;
Solid coding skills in Python/C/C++/Java;
Strong self-motivation and be able to work independently;
Strong communication skills, the ability to communicate effectively and manage relationships with stakeholders coming from both technical and non-technical backgrounds; and
Fluent in English, good written and oral communication skills.
Initial appointment will be offered on a fixed-term contract of two years. Re-appointment thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement and availability of funding.

Rank and salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.

Application Procedure:

Applications are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Those not invited for interview 4 months after submission of application may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University’s Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.

The University reserves the right not to make an appointment for the posts advertised, and the appointment will be made according to terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.

Review of applications is ongoing until the positions are filled.
